history.content: I can't speak to 192 from personal experience, but I'd HIGHLY recommend you take EE 120 before EE C128. If you're not familiar with the Laplace transform going in, you'll have a rough time. I believe 192 also recommends 120 as a prereq.

children.subject: Definitely not. 192, the mechatronics class, is basically a project class where you apply all your knowledge to make something of your choice; with just 16a/b you don't know enough to do something meaningful/fulfilling (most likely, maybe if you've interned or something things may be different).  And for 128, you should really take 120 first- control systems are designed in the laplace (continuous) or Z domains (digital/discrete) domains- if you don't know what those are beforehand, you probably should not take the class (120 is a great class anyways!).

history.content:
Can one EEC128 or EE192 after EE16AB? I would have finished EECS126, Cs170, CS188/189.

Since EE192 is offered once year, can one take it without EEC128 first? Please share your experience with these courses.
history.subject: EE C128 vs EE192
